text:
Emphasised are bad movies.
 In fact, I can't even tell if we're dealing with bad movies or bad lists.
When we start with the first of the big bad directors (The Phantom Menace; "Tachyon Shock"), at least the following is noted: - "Tachyon Shock is one of the worst movies of the 80s". - "Jia Qing, the one Chinese woman who could translate to a screenwriter, wrote all the dialogue. Finally, having run out of material, director of the movie Zhang Ziyi decided to hire a Chinese actor, Li Xiaolin, and to find a way to write out the script she had recorded." - It's "probably" gross. - There is an actual cliffhanger ending.
And that's it.
From the subsequent list - 
The Invisible Women (1998);
Moby Dick (1984); and 
The Da Vinci Code (1538); 
Once Upon a Country (1966);
The Great Beauty (1954);
O Brother, Where Art Thou? (2009)
All were highly underrated and probably worse than they really were. Not likely to persuade the audiences of a film with so high a ranking.
